    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1976-04-13T11:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1976-04-13T11:08:00-05:00" n="346"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <head>346. Memorandum of Conversation, Washington, April 13, 1976, 11:08–11:30
                        a.m.<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d346fn1">Source: <persName
                            corresp="#p_ford-gerald-r">Ford</persName> Library, National Security
                        Adviser, Memoranda of Conversation, April 13, 1976. Secret; <gloss
                            target="#t_nodis">Nodis</gloss>. The meeting was held in the Oval
                        Office. <persName corresp="#p_ford-gerald-r">Ford</persName>’s talking
                        points from <persName corresp="#p_scowcroft-brent">Scowcroft</persName>,
                        which the President saw, assert that the meeting “is meant as a courtesy
                        call to welcome Secretary <persName corresp="#p_romulo-carlos"
                            >Romulo</persName> to the United States and to underline the importance
                        you attach to our military base negotiations which began on April 12, as
                        well as our bilateral economic negotiations which started March 29.”</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d346fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_ford-gerald-r">Ford</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_romulo-carlos">Romulo</persName>, and <persName
                            corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">Kissinger</persName> discussed U.S.
                        politics and the base negotiations.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1976-04-13T11:08:00-05:00" to="1976-04-13T11:30:00-05:00"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date">April 13, 1976, 11:08–11:30
                            a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>MEMORANDUM<lb/>THE WHITE HOUSE<lb/>WASHINGTON</p>
                <p>MEMORANDUM OF CONVERSATION</p>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS:</head>
                    <item>President <persName corresp="#p_ford-gerald-r">Ford</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_romulo-carlos">Carlos P. Romulo</persName>, Secretary
                        of Foreign Affairs, The Philippines</item>
                    <item>Secretary <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">Kissinger</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Brent <persName corresp="#p_scowcroft-brent">Scowcroft</persName>,
                        Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_amb">Amb</gloss>. Eduardo Romualdez, Philippine
                        Ambassador</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_enrile-juan-ponce">Juan Ponce Enrile</persName>,
                        Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_amb">Amb</gloss>. <persName corresp="#p_habib-philip-c"
                            >Philip C. Habib</persName>, Assistant Secretary of State for East Asian
                        and Pacific Affairs</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_amb">Amb</gloss>. <persName
                            corresp="#p_sullivan-william-h">William H. Sullivan</persName>, US
                        Ambassador to the Philippines</item>
                </list>
                <p>DATE AND TIME: Tuesday, April 13, 1976<lb/>11:08 - 11:30 a.m.<lb/>PLACE: The Oval
                    Office</p>
                <p>[The press enters and takes photographs. There is discussion of the President’s
                    wartime experience in the Philippines. The press departs.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_romulo-carlos">Romulo</persName>: I have been asked by the
                    President to express his greetings, and he hopes for a successful
                    negotiation.</p>
                <p>The President: Please convey my greetings to the President and Mrs. <persName
                        corresp="#p_marcos-imelda-romualdez">Marcos</persName> and my thanks for a
                    marvelous greeting and my visit. I am going to return to play golf sometime.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_romulo-carlos">Romulo</persName>: The President asked us
                    not to do anything which would interfere with your reelection.</p>
                <p>The President: That is very thoughtful.</p>
            </div>
